  "prompt": "What is wrong with Yahoo Answers?",
  "response": "Yahoo Answers was a popular question-and-answer website that was shut down on May 4, 2021, after nearly 16 years of operation. Some of the main issues that led to its decline and eventual closure included:\n\n1. Low-quality content: Many questions and answers were poorly written, nonsensical, or inappropriate.\n\n2. Trolling and joke responses: Users often posted deliberately unhelpful or humorous answers instead of serious information.\n\n3. Lack of moderation: The platform struggled to effectively moderate content and filter out inappropriate responses.\n\n4. Declining user base: As other platforms like Quora and Reddit gained popularity, Yahoo Answers saw a significant decrease in active users.\n\n5. Outdated design: The website's interface and user experience became increasingly outdated compared to modern platforms.\n\n6. Unreliable information: Many answers were inaccurate, biased, or based on personal opinions rather than factual information.\n\nThese issues ultimately contributed to Yahoo's decision to discontinue the service, redirecting users to other resources.",
